# {{appName}}

> AKARI MCP-Declarative Tier App — `{{appId}}`

## Overview

{{appName}} is a [MCP-Declarative Tier](https://github.com/akari-os/akari-os/docs/sdd/specs/spec-akari-app-sdk.md) AKARI app.
MCP-Declarative apps use a bundled MCP server and a `panel.schema.json` declaration
to provide UI in the Shell without writing any React code.

**When to use MCP-Declarative over Full Tier:**
- Your UI fits a form / list / tabs layout (HUB-025 standard widgets are sufficient)
- You want the lightest possible review path (Automated Lint + Contract Test only)
- You are wrapping an existing API or MCP endpoint

**Upgrade path:** Start MCP-Declarative → promote to Full Tier later by changing
`tier = "full"` in `akari.toml` and adding a React panel (no data migration needed).

## Requirements

- Node.js >= 18
- AKARI OS with SDK `{{sdkRange}}`

## Development

```bash
npm install
akari dev          # start dev server and mount into local Shell
```

## Certification

```bash
akari app certify   # Automated Lint + Contract Tests (HUB-024 §6.8)
                    # For MCP-Declarative: validates MCP tool contracts against panel.schema.json
```

## Distribution

```bash
# Self-distribution (Automated Lint + Contract Test only)
npm publish

# AKARI Marketplace (lighter Manual Review — schema + MCP contract audit only)
akari app publish
```

## Structure

```
{{appSlug}}/
├── akari.toml              App manifest (AKARI-HUB-024 §6.5)
├── panel.schema.json       Panel Schema v0 declaration (AKARI-HUB-025)
└── mcp-server/
    ├── index.ts            MCP server entry point (@modelcontextprotocol/sdk)
    └── tools.ts            Tool implementations (bound to panel.schema.json actions)
```

## Panel Schema

`panel.schema.json` declares the app's UI using [AKARI Panel Schema v0](https://github.com/akari-os/akari-os/docs/sdd/specs/spec-akari-panel-schema.md) (HUB-025).
The Shell's generic Schema Renderer draws the UI; no React code is required.

Key concepts:
- `fields[].bind` — connects UI inputs to MCP tool arguments or local state
- `actions[].mcp` — wires buttons to MCP tool calls
- `actions[].hitl` — gates actions behind a human-approval dialog (HUB-024 §6.6 Permission API)
- `{{t:key}}` — i18n keys resolved from `locales` at the bottom of the schema

## Guidelines

- All persistent state goes through Pool / AMP — no local DB (HUB-024 §6.7 rule 2)
- All `amp.record()` calls must include `goal_ref` (HUB-024 §6.6)
- Declare only necessary permissions in `akari.toml` (rule 5)
- MCP tools declared in `akari.toml [mcp].tools` MUST be implemented in `mcp-server/`

